text: Jeep Tshering Lama (alt. forename: Jip; alt. middle names: Tsering, Chiring, Chhiring) is a Nepali politician and a member of the House of Representatives of the federal parliament of Nepal. He was elected from Nepali Congress under the proportional representation system, filling the reserved seat for indigenous groups. In 2018, he donated five ambulances to local governments in Dolakha district. ==References== Category:Living people Category:Nepalese politicians Category:Year of birth missing (living people)
